d labor and many other factors have, of course, contributed, it seems clear to Getman that the Supreme Court has played an important role in transforming the law and defeating policies that support the labor movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLabor laws and legislationzUnited StatesxCases. 0aLabor laws and legislationzUnited StatesxInterpretation and construction. 0aLabor unionsxLaw and legislationzUnited StatesxCases. 4aLabor History. 4aLegal History & Studies. 4aU.S. History.  aLabor unions, Supreme Court, labor law, labor relations, dispute resolution, labor movement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170365240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501703652423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501703652/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles